{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Single Page — List + Detail\n      One \"Cohortisation\" page. Top section: cohort cards (like pathway list). Click a cohort to expand into detail view showing criteria, scoring engine, population stats. Business users see the same page — the population dashboard is part of each cohort's detail.\n      \n        /dashboard/cohortisation\n          ├─ Cohort list (cards: name, condition, patient count, tier breakdown mini-chart)\n          ├─ [+ Create Cohort] button\n          └─ Click card → /dashboard/cohortisation/:id\n              ├─ Tab: Population (distribution chart, risk pool stats, patient table)\n              ├─ Tab: Criteria (eligibility rules editor)\n              ├─ Tab: Scoring Engine (optional — component builder, weights, tiers)\n              └─ Tab: Linked Pathways (which pathways reference this cohort)\n      \n      \n        ProsEverything in one placeNatural drill-down from list → detailMirrors the pathway list → editor pattern\n        ConsBusiness user has to know which cohort to clickNo cross-cohort population overview","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775557449580}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Split — Population Dashboard + Cohort Builder\n      Two sub-pages under Cohortisation. The default view is a population dashboard (all cohorts, cross-cohort stats, risk pool overview). A separate \"Cohort Builder\" sub-page is where architects create/edit cohort definitions.\n      \n        /dashboard/cohortisation (default: Population Dashboard)\n          ├─ Cross-cohort population overview (total members, unassigned, tier distribution per cohort)\n          ├─ Cohort summary cards (name, member count, avg CRS, trending arrows)\n          ├─ Risk pool table (filterable by cohort, tier, condition)\n          └─ [Manage Cohorts →] link\n        \n        /dashboard/cohortisation/builder (Cohort Builder)\n          ├─ Cohort list + [Create Cohort]\n          └─ /dashboard/cohortisation/builder/:id\n              ├─ Criteria editor\n              ├─ Scoring engine (optional)\n              └─ Preview (run against population, see who matches)\n      \n      \n        ProsBusiness user lands on dashboard — sees risk pools immediatelyBuilder is separate, focused workspace for architectsCross-cohort view answers \"how is our population distributed?\"\n        ConsTwo sub-pages to maintainNavigation between dashboard and builder could feel disconnected","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775557466963}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Dashboard-First with Inline Builder\n      Population dashboard is the landing page. Each cohort card is expandable — click to see detail + edit criteria inline. Creating a new cohort opens a slide-over panel or dialog, not a new page. Keeps everything in one flow.\n      \n        /dashboard/cohortisation\n          ├─ Population overview bar (total members, assigned %, unassigned count)\n          ├─ Cohort cards grid (each card: name, condition, member count, mini tier chart)\n          │   └─ Click card → expands inline: criteria summary, scoring summary, population table\n          │       └─ [Edit Cohort] → sheet/drawer with full criteria + scoring editor\n          ├─ [+ Create Cohort] → sheet/drawer with builder\n          └─ Risk pool table (all members, filterable by cohort/tier)\n      \n      \n        ProsSingle page, no navigationDashboard-first for business usersEditing is contextual (drawer), not a page switch\n        ConsDrawer may be too cramped for complex scoring engine configInline expansion can get cluttered with many cohorts","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1775557478928}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Split — Population Dashboard + Cohort Builder\n      Two sub-pages under Cohortisation. The default view is a population dashboard (all cohorts, cross-cohort stats, risk pool overview). A separate \"Cohort Builder\" sub-page is where architects create/edit cohort definitions.\n      \n        /dashboard/cohortisation (default: Population Dashboard)\n          ├─ Cross-cohort population overview (total members, unassigned, tier distribution per cohort)\n          ├─ Cohort summary cards (name, member count, avg CRS, trending arrows)\n          ├─ Risk pool table (filterable by cohort, tier, condition)\n          └─ [Manage Cohorts →] link\n        \n        /dashboard/cohortisation/builder (Cohort Builder)\n          ├─ Cohort list + [Create Cohort]\n          └─ /dashboard/cohortisation/builder/:id\n              ├─ Criteria editor\n              ├─ Scoring engine (optional)\n              └─ Preview (run against population, see who matches)\n      \n      \n        ProsBusiness user lands on dashboard — sees risk pools immediatelyBuilder is separate, focused workspace for architectsCross-cohort view answers \"how is our population distributed?\"\n        ConsTwo sub-pages to maintainNavigation between dashboard and builder could feel disconnected","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775557491430}
