{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Table-Based Builder\n      A structured form. The architect adds scoring components as rows in a table. Each component expands to show its scoring rules (also a table of criterion → points). Weights are sliders/inputs at the component level. Tier thresholds are a separate table below.\n      \n        Component Table:\n        \n          ComponentData SourceWeightRules\n          Glycaemic ControlLabs → HbA1c35%5 rules ▸\n          Complication BurdenDiagnoses + Labs25%12 rules ▸\n          AdherencePharmacy → PDC20%4 rules ▸\n          + Add Component\n        \n        Expanding \"Glycaemic Control\" shows its scoring rules table inline.\n      \n      \n        ProsCompact, data-dense — architects see everything at onceFamiliar spreadsheet-like interactionEasy to add/remove/reorder components\n        ConsCan feel overwhelming with many rulesNo visual sense of how components relate","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1775557646913}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Card-Based Builder\n      Each scoring component is a card. Cards show the component name, weight (as a visual bar), data source, and rule count. Click a card to open a drawer/panel where you configure that component's scoring rules. Tier thresholds shown as a visual gradient bar below the cards.\n      \n        \n          \n            Glycaemic Control\n            \n            35% · Labs · 5 rules\n          \n          \n            Complication Burden\n            \n            25% · Diagnoses · 12 rules\n          \n          \n            Adherence\n            \n            20% · Pharmacy · 4 rules\n          \n        \n        + Add Component\n        Click any card → opens side drawer with scoring rules editor\n      \n      \n        ProsVisual weight representation at a glanceLess overwhelming — details are hidden until neededConsistent with \"card\" pattern used elsewhere in the app\n        ConsMore clicks to see all rules (open each drawer)Can't compare components side by side easily","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775557687197}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Card-Based Builder\n      Each scoring component is a card. Cards show the component name, weight (as a visual bar), data source, and rule count. Click a card to open a drawer/panel where you configure that component's scoring rules. Tier thresholds shown as a visual gradient bar below the cards.\n      \n        \n          \n            Glycaemic Control\n            \n            35% · Labs · 5 rules\n          \n          \n            Complication Burden\n            \n            25% · Diagnoses · 12 rules\n          \n          \n            Adherence\n            \n            20% · Pharmacy · 4 rules\n          \n        \n        + Add Component\n        Click any card → opens side drawer with scoring rules editor\n      \n      \n        ProsVisual weight representation at a glanceLess overwhelming — details are hidden until neededConsistent with \"card\" pattern used elsewhere in the app\n        ConsMore clicks to see all rules (open each drawer)Can't compare components side by side easily","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775557691828}
